Before doing the vector search, derive the user’s intent from the current message plus the selected history: use recent history if the user is referring back implicitly, or use the quoted-message slice if they replied to a specific WhatsApp message. Then rewrite that into a new, unambiguous internal query and run vector search on that rewritten query instead of the raw user message, so RAG retrieves the most relevant catalog items. The rewrite only affects vector search; the AI prompt still gets the selected history plus the retrieved catalog context. This belongs in the bot/RAG path, not the API or worker jobs.

For example, in this chat, the user is asking for more details about the 3rd product. If we vector-search only the latest message, the retrieved items can be unrelated, and the AI ends up writing the answer from bad catalog context. In short: garbage retrieval input produces garbage retrieval output, which then produces an incorrect final answer.